    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan:\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**9 files** to modify/create across 4 layers:\n\n### New files\n- **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** — core implementation\n- **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** — integration tests\n\n### Modified files\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` preview feature (with `as_str` and `FromStr` entries for `\"cache-stats\"`)\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` and a `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (mirrors `SizeArgs`)\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — add `mod cache_stats;` + re-export\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats`\n5. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — add `cache_stats()` command builder and `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter helper\n6. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — register `mod cache_stats;`\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/show_settings.rs`** — update two insta snapshots that enumerate all `PreviewFeature` variants\n\n### Key design decisions\n- **Reuses `CacheBucket::iter()`** which already yields all 10 buckets in canonical order — `Python` is intentionally excluded (it's absent from `iter()` in the existing code)\n- **Per-bucket `DiskUsage` calls** via the existing `diskus` dependency; `bucket_path.exists()` guards against uninitialized buckets\n- **Total is a sum of per-bucket values** (not a second root-tree walk) so it's internally consistent\n- **`--human` / `-H`** flag exactly mirrors `cache size` — reuses the existing `human_readable_bytes()` already re-exported from `uv-console`\n- **Preview-gated** with `CacheStats` feature, warning message pattern matches `cache size`'s wording",
